fields.Title: WHIRLING F3 / CLEAR WINDOW VISCAL DIFFICULT
fields.Description: This window has been recently replaced. High perception to notice. This dialogue gets a viscal and becomes trivial once someone admits Assassination
fields.Placement: the window on the right, in klaasje's room

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Shit I know this..." His voice is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shit I know this..." His voice is excited as he nods approvingly. "Cuno gets this shit. Ballistics shit, science shit."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Indeed. Neither do I.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Indeed. Neither do I."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A powerful gust of wind coming in f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A powerful gust of wind coming in from the bay rattles the windowpane.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A vague sense of disappointment fil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A vague sense of disappointment fills you. The glass shimmers as if taunting you with its secrets.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. On the contrary, this whole ro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. On the contrary, this whole room could be very useful if we could read it." He looks down the stairs. "Maybe later."

fields.Title: Clear Window: "The window stands mute in the frame..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The window stands mute in the frame. The wind picks up outside.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "72%. With an antique weapon that fi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: 72%. With an antique weapon that fires military-grade ammunition -- a Belle-Magrave rifle, for example. This is a good short distance, but not too short. The perpetrator aimed with their back against the railing, or possibly kneeling for precision. This would explain why it only took them one shot.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant leans closer. "You'r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant leans closer. "You're thinking -- what if the shot didn't come from the roof?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "B' for boardwalk; B'' for Land's En..."
fields.Dialogue Text: B' for boardwalk; B'' for Land's End and B''' for the islet, detective. There may be smaller points in between, but those are too fine to zoom in on.

fields.Title: You: ""It's *okay*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's *okay*."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "None that you've found thus far. Bu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: None that you've found thus far. But that doesn't mean there aren't any.

fields.Title: You: "I've *sort of* ruled out this locat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I've *sort of* ruled out this location.

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe we need to go to the island?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe we need to go to the island?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The makings of a sniper's nest."
fields.Dialogue Text: The makings of a sniper's nest.

fields.Title: You: ""I think the shot might have come f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think the shot might have come from the islet."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "She had a long time to think about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She had a long time to think about it after. Standing on that roof -- staring at the glass...

fields.Title: Clear Window: "Smooth as ice. There are spots of m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smooth as ice. There are spots of mud and rain on the outside. Even smudges. But the surface of the window is clear from the inside. No chips, no hairline fractures.

fields.Title: Logic: "I was being sarcastic. It was estab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was being sarcastic. It was established that *you* did it. Anyway.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's a weakness," he admits after..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a weakness," he admits after a pause, looking in the direction of the stairs.

fields.Title: You: "Have a look at point B''' -- the is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have a look at point B''' -- the islet.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The shot would have been a small mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The shot would have been a small miracle: 5% likelihood. There *is* an extremely narrow field of view from the bay to the window, between Rue de Saint Ghislaine 10 and 33A. The angle would have been extreme and access to the islets is questionable...
fields.Alternate1: The shot would have been a small miracle: 5% likelihood. There *is* an extremely narrow field of view from the bay to the window, between Rue de Saint Ghislaine 8B and 33A. The angle would have been extreme and access to the islets is questionable... but! It is a possibility.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The shot had to come from a greater..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The shot had to come from a greater distance -- beyond A'. Should we extrapolate to include *every* possible point of origin in Martinaise?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It also looks like there may be mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It also looks like there may be more to her skill set than we know. The question is -- should we trust her?"

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, yeah. Let's not go to th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, yeah. Let's not go to the island." (No go.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, but it'll take them days to g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, but it'll take them days to give it to us."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I find that hard to believe. But a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I find that hard to believe. But at this point... what difference does it make?"

fields.Title: You: ""I remember an anti-aircraft gun. O..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I remember an anti-aircraft gun. Or the ruins of one... on the island. From the coin operated viewer."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: You: "Is she trying to tell me the shot c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is she trying to tell me the shot came from the islet?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You see the same two neon lit shape..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see the same two neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. Only now a red thread bisects the room, pointing from the antenna outside, to the cupboard on the wall.

fields.Title: Horrific Necktie: "Stop distracting him, he has work t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop distracting him, he has work to do -- plus, if I recall, the window had been giving him shit ever since he got here.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm not exactly sure either, to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not exactly sure either, to be honest. My imagination has a way of failing me."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: You: "More precisely?"
fields.Dialogue Text: More precisely?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Indeed. There was no evidence of a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Indeed. There was no evidence of a sniper's nest in that location. The distance is too great and water vapour would have made the shot almost impossible.

fields.Title: You: ""You seem unenthusiastic.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You seem unenthusiastic."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant sighs, looking into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant sighs, looking into the cold distance across the water...
fields.Alternate1: The wind blows in from the open window. The lieutenant sighs, looking into the cold distance across the water...

fields.Title: You: ""This is her way of saying she's so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is her way of saying she's sorry."

fields.Title: You: "I extrapolated all the points of or..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I extrapolated all the points of origin. Now, where does the thread lead?

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, yeah. Let's not go to th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, yeah. Let's not go to the island."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""The island?" He scoffs. "Cuno ain'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The island?" He scoffs. "Cuno ain't afraid of fucking *anything*, pig."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The island in the bay."
fields.Dialogue Text: The island in the bay.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The golden light melts away into th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The golden light melts away into the blue, glassy darkness of your mind. In it are two neon lit shapes: a man and a woman on the single bed.

fields.Title: You: "What is this, *guilt* now?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What is this, *guilt* now?

fields.Title: You: "Could the shot have come from *insi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could the shot have come from *inside* the room? A closer point...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Point X would contradict the woman'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Point X would contradict the woman's testimony, rendering the entire proposition void. These figures would be wiped out, detective.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm just being thorough.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just being thorough."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It would be the *diligent* thing t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It would be the *diligent* thing to do. Until then -- personally -- I'm going with the roof version. A simple hypothesis can be wrong, but it's something to build on."
fields.Alternate1: "It would be the *diligent* thing to do. Until then, personally, I'm going with the roof version. It fits the hidden path through the Whirling. A simple hypothesis."

fields.Title: Clear Window: "This window is pristine, at least o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This window is pristine, at least on the inside. A red thread has been taped to the glass using adhesive tape. It trembles ever so slightly in the cold wind.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The red thread bisecting the room s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The red thread bisecting the room shows the trajectory of the bullet.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""She was there that night -- she wo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She was there that night -- she would have known precisely where the bullet hole was in the glass..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks out the window..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks out the window and onto the bay.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ah... Yes, of course. The village...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah... Yes, of course. The village. Let's go."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No-no. We're onto something... We..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no. We're onto something... We should come back with a map and compare the landscape to the radius of the shot."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""To do, you mean? Nothing. Harbour'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To do, you mean? Nothing. Harbour's closed, everyone's dead. This scene is dead, pig."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, why fucking not?" He spits o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, why fucking not?" He spits on the floor. "Just one question, though --"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm going to the island.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm going to the island."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The island in the bay."
fields.Dialogue Text: The island in the bay.

fields.Title: Volition: "It's not something he's proud of, b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not something he's proud of, but that's the way it is.

fields.Title: You: "Extrapolate the radius to include a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Extrapolate the radius to include all of Martinaise.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The man does not know the bullet ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man does not know the bullet has entered his brain. He never will. Death comes faster than the realization.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "72%. With a weapon that fires jacke..."
fields.Dialogue Text: 72%. With a weapon that fires jacketed ammunition -- likely a rifle. This is a good short distance, but not too short. The perpetrator aimed with their back against the railing, or possibly kneeling for precision. This would explain why it only took them one shot.

fields.Title: You: ""This is also the only point of ori..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also the only point of origin we haven't ruled out yet." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: You: ""This is also one of the few places..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also one of the few places in Martinaise we haven't been to." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"]  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Nothing scares you now."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing scares you now.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Of course. The village on the coast..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course. The village on the coast. Let's go.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "The lieutenant would probably agree..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant would probably agree that, in this situation, it's best to be thorough.

fields.Title: You: "Look around."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look around.

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno. I think the shot might have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno. I think the shot might have come from the islet."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You know which window has *not* bee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know which window has *not* been recently replaced?

fields.Title: You: "Didn't we establish that someone el..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Didn't we establish that someone else did that?
fields.Alternate1: Didn't we establish that someone else was responsible -- the person who also forced all the drinks in me?

fields.Title: You: ""This is bullshit. Bullshit window.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is bullshit. Bullshit window."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I see you have given this a lot of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I see you have given this a lot of thought," he remarks, raising an eyebrow. "Are those the locations you've singled out, in addition to the roof? And what is the likelihood, in your opinion, that it came from a further distance?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is ballistics. She's left a t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is ballistics. She's left a trajectory for us..." The lieutenant tests the thread with his finger. Drawn taut, it rebounds instantly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't know. At this point..." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know. At this point..." He stops mid-sentence.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. I just don't want to walk into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I just don't want to walk into another *embarrassment*. I am a creature of pride, you see..." There is silence. "I'm afraid of becoming a joke."

fields.Title: You: ""Is Klaasje trying to tell us the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is Klaasje trying to tell us the shot came from the islet?"

fields.Title: You: "How did she know how to do this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How did she know how to do this?

fields.Title: You: "This is also a location I have yet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is also a location I have yet to rule out... (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: You: "So the shot could have come from so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So the shot could have come from somewhere further out than the roof...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It is possible that it came from B..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is possible that it came from B prime (the boardwalk), B double prime (Land's End), or B triple prime (the islet).

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You can't know for sure until you i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can't know for sure until you investigate those locations.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The island in the bay."
fields.Dialogue Text: The island in the bay.

fields.Title: Logic: "In the bookstore!"
fields.Dialogue Text: In the bookstore!

fields.Title: You: "Blink. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Blink. [Leave.]

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It suggests the bullet came from th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It suggests the bullet came from the extreme upper quadrant of possible angles -- from a point beyond the roof: B'''.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "He is trying to justify it to himse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is trying to justify it to himself.

fields.Title: You: ""You're not... afraid, are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not... afraid, are you?"

fields.Title: You: "Actually, I don't want to go to the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Actually, I don't want to go to the island.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Danger? Another trap?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Danger? Another trap?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The man is kneeling, the woman is o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man is kneeling, the woman is on her back. It's the night of March 4th and a shot has just been fired.
fields.Alternate1: Like the witness said -- the man is kneeling, the woman is on her back. It's the night of March 4th and a shot has just been fired.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The golden light melts away into th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The golden light melts away into the blue, glassy darkness of your mind. In it are two neon lit shapes: a man and a woman on the single bed.

fields.Title: You: ""I just don't know.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I just don't know."

fields.Title: Authority: "He's used to knowing who to trust...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's used to knowing who to trust. This makes him uncomfortable.

fields.Title: You: "This is also a location I have yet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is also a location I have yet to rule out... (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: You: "Inspect the ghostly figures."
fields.Dialogue Text: Inspect the ghostly figures.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There was a map in the bookstore...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There was a map in the bookstore. We should come back with it, compare the landscape to the radius of the shot."

fields.Title: You: "Have a look at point B'' -- Land's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have a look at point B'' -- Land's End.

fields.Title: You: "Are there any arguments against A p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Are there any arguments against A prime, the roof?

fields.Title: You: "I have ruled out this location."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have ruled out this location.

fields.Title: You: ""What else is there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else is there?"

fields.Title: You: ""You're not... afraid, are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not... afraid, are you?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I understand.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I understand."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Could be the makings of a sniper's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could be the makings of a sniper's nest..." He nods.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Oh..." The boy's eyes dart back an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh..." The boy's eyes dart back and forth. "The village on the coast. Yeah, you do that."

fields.Title: Logic: "The lead is flimsy, but *what else..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lead is flimsy, but *what else is there*? The alternative is going around Martinaise looking under every rock and talking to every person.

fields.Title: You: "I remember an anti-aircraft gun. Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I remember an anti-aircraft gun. The ruins of one... on the island.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We need to do ballistics on this -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We need to do ballistics on this -- understand where the shot came from once and for all."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It's not the roof -- and you would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not the roof -- and you would have found it had it been on the coast, in either B prime or B double prime, which leaves...
fields.Alternate1: It's not the roof -- and had it come from the coast, you would have probably stumbled upon it while you were running around over there. This leaves...
fields.Alternate2: It's not the roof -- so it had to come from the coast or the island. You should probably start with the coast. It's closer and doesn't require you to do a lot of swimming.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "According to your map of the distri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: According to your map of the district, this shot could have come from a wide angle of locations -- starting with the northern edge of the abandoned boardwalk, ending with an islet in the bay. Let's call them B prime.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Islet, technically. But yes. It loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Islet, technically. But yes. It looks more and more probable.

fields.Title: You: ""This is also a location we have ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also a location we have yet to rule out." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: "What position are they in?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What position are they in?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "According to your map of the distri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: According to your map of the district, this shot could have come from a wide angle of locations -- starting with the northern edge of the abandoned boardwalk, ending with an islet in the bay. Let's call them B prime.

fields.Title: You: "I have the map -- extrapolate the r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have the map -- extrapolate the radius to include all of Martinaise.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Then there's the thread the witness..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then there's the thread the witness left. She *did* have a first-hand view of the event. Perhaps she found something in the outer reaches of her memory of it...
fields.Alternate1: Then there's the thread the witness left. She *did* have a first hand view of the event. Perhaps she found something in the outer reaches of her memory of it... you need to inspect it *again*.

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, that's not gonna work. There..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, that's not gonna work. There must be something else we've missed."

fields.Title: You: ""I have no idea. Don't we have... a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have no idea. Don't we have... a boat?"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There, across the grey water -- ami..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, across the grey water -- amidst crumbling concrete, a birch tree... and the half-sunken ruins of a flak tower.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't have anything to say. This..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't have anything to say. This is just something we have to do, Kim."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good. We should come back with the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. We should come back with the map and compare the landscape to the radius of the shot."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Pig..." The kid looks at you with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Pig..." The kid looks at you with something akin to admiration. "You're really fucking on to something there."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, Cuno's seen that shit. Crazy..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, Cuno's seen that shit. Crazy shit. Ain't nothing to Cuno, but lots of places to hide there."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""How are you gonna *get* to the isl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How are you gonna *get* to the island? Cuno has his ways, but that ain't for your fat old ass."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Aw, fuck, pig. We totally gotta go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aw, fuck, pig. We totally gotta go to the island now." He pumps a fist in the air. "Tryna not go to the island... Just one Q."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Your voice sounds hollow in the des..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice sounds hollow in the deserted room... you are alone.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A ray of backward motion explodes f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth: through the window, to the roof outside, widening into a radius -- A prime.
fields.Alternate1: A ray of backward motion explodes from his mouth to the roof outside -- A prime -- to then widen into a radius of locations in Martinaise: B prime, B double prime, and B triple prime.

fields.Title: Logic: "You need to understand where that s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You need to understand where that shot came from -- once and for all.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Following your lead, the lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Following your lead, the lieutenant leans in closer to inspect the surface.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Whatever it is, it's messing with y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whatever it is, it's messing with your concentration.
fields.Alternate1: Maybe it isn't. I mean, 24 Hour Window is out of business. What were your options?

fields.Title: You: "So I'm what... 80% sure the roof is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So I'm what... 80% sure the roof is where the shot was made from?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "One kilometre away. A point beyond..."
fields.Dialogue Text: One kilometre away. A point beyond the docks, on an islet in the bay. The fort is ruined but the perpetrator may have found a stable spot on the beaches surrounding it, where the concrete crumbles into the sea -- as you saw in the coin operated viewer...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Indeed, there *was* a possible snip..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Indeed, there *was* a possible sniper's nest underneath the boardwalk but no one had been there in months, if not years.

fields.Title: Logic: "It still remains an odd coincidence..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It still remains an odd coincidence that there was a bunker there...

fields.Title: You: ""This is also a location we have ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also a location we have yet to rule out." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""So it is.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So it is."

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, let's go to the fucking islan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, let's go to the fucking island." (Go!)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay, let's go to the fucking isla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, let's go to the fucking island." He takes a second to gather himself, then says...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. There's nothing else..." He si..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. There's nothing else..." He sighs, looking into the cold distance across the water.
fields.Alternate1: "No. There's nothing else..." The wind blows in from the open window. He sighs, looking into the cold distance across the water.

fields.Title: You: ""I have no idea. Don't we have... a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have no idea. Don't we have... a boat?"

fields.Title: You: ""What else is there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else is there?"

fields.Title: Logic: "The lead is flimsy. You might as we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lead is flimsy. You might as well go around Martinaise looking under every rock and talking to every person -- but *what else is there*?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "She was there that night -- she wou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was there that night -- she would have known precisely where the bullet hole was in the glass.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "But how will you get to the island?"
fields.Dialogue Text: But how will you get to the island?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You have to go to the island. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have to go to the island. It's where the threads all meet...

fields.Title: Clear Window: "Light from the desk lamp reflects o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Light from the desk lamp reflects off the glass in an untarnished golden halo. The glass is pristine and utterly silent.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The same two neon lit shapes -- a m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The same two neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth, through the window, to the roof outside, widening into a radius -- A prime.
fields.Alternate1: A red thread runs through the neon lit shapes of a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth to the roof outside, to then widen into a radius of locations in Martinaise: B prime, B double prime, and B triple prime.
fields.Alternate2: A red thread runs through the neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth, through the window, to the roof outside, widening into a radius: A prime.
fields.Alternate3: Two neon-lit shapes: a man and a woman having sex. A ray of backward motion explodes from his mouth to the roof outside -- A prime -- to then widen into a radius of locations in Martinaise: B prime, B double prime, and B triple prime.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "...what difference does it make?"
fields.Dialogue Text: ...what difference does it make?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The golden light melts away into th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The golden light melts away into the blue, glassy darkness of your mind. In it are two neon lit shapes: a man and a woman on the single bed.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The same two neon lit shapes -- a m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The same two neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth, through the window, to the roof outside, widening into a radius -- A prime.
fields.Alternate1: A red thread runs through the neon lit shapes of a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth to the roof outside, to then widen into a radius of locations in Martinaise: B prime, B double prime, and B triple prime.
fields.Alternate2: A red thread runs through the neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. A ray of backward motion explodes from the man's mouth, through the window, to the roof outside, widening into a radius: A prime.
fields.Alternate3: Two neon-lit shapes: a man and a woman having sex. A ray of backward motion explodes from his mouth to the roof outside -- A prime -- to then widen into a radius of locations in Martinaise: B prime, B double prime, and B triple prime.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You get the feeling this room would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You get the feeling this room would tell you something crucial if you only knew how to listen...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The ray cast from the man's mouth u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The ray cast from the man's mouth unravels into a fan of possible directions, all on the roof at first. The shot could have come from any of them. This is composite location A prime -- most likely of the origin points.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "That's a 28%, yes. In this model th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's a 28%, yes. In this model the shot *could* have come from a greater distance. Nothing excludes the possibility. Should we extrapolate to include *every* possible point of origin in Martinaise?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The lights were on in here. Outside..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lights were on in here. Outside it was dark. It was like shooting fish in an aquarium -- a well lit aquarium. The victim opened his mouth to let the bullet in. Neither of them would have seen anything outside, in the darkness -- too busy with their own bodies.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Ruby ruled this out vehemently. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ruby ruled this out vehemently. The shot would have been heard from downstairs -- where no one heard it. The likelihood of A' has fallen drastically. You may be looking for a sniper.

fields.Title: Empathy: "For a second he seems... tired."
fields.Dialogue Text: For a second he seems... tired.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno's got no fucking clue." He lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno's got no fucking clue." He looks at you. "You need to pig this shit. Cop-style."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Totally what a sniper would use."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Totally what a sniper would use." He squints. "Aircraft gun."

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno, let's go to the fucking isla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno, let's go to the fucking island."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Fuck yeah I'm in." He spits on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck yeah I'm in." He spits on the floor.

fields.Title: You: "Lilienne, the Net Picker. She's tar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lilienne, the Net Picker. She's tarring her boat...

fields.Title: You: "I have no idea. Don't we have... a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have no idea. Don't we have... a boat?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You see the same two neon lit shape..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see the same two neon lit shapes -- a man and a woman. Only now a red thread bisects the room, pointing from the antenna outside, to the cupboard on the wall.

fields.Title: Logic: "This is amateur ballistics. She lef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is amateur ballistics. She left a trajectory for you...

fields.Title: You: "What *is* the point of origin, damn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What *is* the point of origin, damn it!?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's not impossible." He nods. "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not impossible." He nods. "There is a narrow opening between the commercial area and the collapsed tenement north of it..."

fields.Title: Empathy: "He doesn't *really* believe this wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't *really* believe this will yield anything.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "He wrote: *The Cunn*."
fields.Dialogue Text: He wrote: *The Cunn*.

fields.Title: Clear Window: "This window is pristine on the insi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This window is pristine on the inside -- unlike the one next to it. Light from the desk lamp reflects off the glass in an untarnished golden halo.

fields.Title: You: "Run your finger across the surface..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Run your finger across the surface of the glass.

fields.Title: You: "The one I smashed in my room?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The one I smashed in my room?

fields.Title: You: ""Tell me again Kim, what are we loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tell me again Kim, what are we looking for here? Ballistics?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is." The lieutenant touches the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is." The lieutenant touches the window. "We're beating our heads against this -- let's go do something more useful."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "From the roof outside -- location A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: From the roof outside -- location A prime. The glass fractures around the bullet hole. Shards face inwards like a corona behind the woman's back...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There could've been. Then the rain..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There could've been. Then the rain and slush and wind washed it away. This was more than a week ago.

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The red thread bisecting the room s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The red thread bisecting the room shows the trajectory of the bullet -- Klaasje has done some amateur ballistics here.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""How do we get there? Joyce Messier..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: ""Not a lot, no.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not a lot, no."

fields.Title: You: ""Lilienne, the Net Picker in the vi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lilienne, the Net Picker in the village. She's tarring her boat..."

fields.Title: Cuno: "The boy squints, looking into the c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The boy squints, looking into the cold distance across the water...
fields.Alternate1: The wind blows in from the open window. The boy squints, looking into the cold distance across the water...

fields.Title: You: "This is also one of the few places..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is also one of the few places in Martinaise I have not been to... (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"]  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: You: "Maybe someone in the fishing villag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe someone in the fishing village can help?

fields.Title: You: "I'm not afraid."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm not afraid.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There, across the grey water -- amo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, across the grey water -- among crumbling concrete, a birch tree... the ruins of a flak tower, remember?

fields.Title: You: "Blink. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Blink. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Where does it come from?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Where does it come from?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "72%. With a weapon that's good for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: 72%. With a weapon that's good for medium range, like a rifle or sports pistol. This is a good short distance, but not too short. The perpetrator aimed with their back against the railing, or possibly kneeling for precision. This would explain why it only took them one shot.

fields.Title: You: ""Hey, where do I get a map of Marti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, where do I get a map of Martinaise?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Seven hundred metres away. The like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seven hundred metres away. The likeliest of these B positions, 20% chance. A skilled sniper could have made the shot, provided he had a safe sniper's nest. Even with the light on inside, we're talking military training. At that distance the perpetrator would have had to take wind direction into account.

fields.Title: You: ""Much less than from the roof, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Much less than from the roof, but still."

fields.Title: Clear Window: "The glass is cold from the air flow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The glass is cold from the air flowing in.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The man looks directly at the woman..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man looks directly at the woman. The shot's possible directions converge in his mouth -- a ray cast from somewhere outside, entering his brain.

fields.Title: Half Light: "He sees danger. Another trap perhap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sees danger. Another trap perhaps? He must be cautious for a reason -- this man has decades of experience.

fields.Title: You: ""How did she know how to do this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How did she know how to do this?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cool shit, sub-zero shit. Cuno's l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool shit, sub-zero shit. Cuno's listening. You got his attention." A nod of approval, then: "So what's next?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm going to the island  -- are yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm going to the island  -- are you in?"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It is. The fucking island awaits."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is. The fucking island awaits.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing.

fields.Title: You: "What else is there?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What else is there?

fields.Title: You: "What happened here?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What happened here?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Your voice alone rings in the room...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice alone rings in the room. This visual forensics ability doesn't dispense shopping tips.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Maybe -- there were boats there. W..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe -- there were boats there. We should ask around. Let's go."

fields.Title: Logic: "The lead is flimsy. You might as we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lead is flimsy. You might as well go around Martinaise looking under every rock and talking to every person -- but *what else is there*?

fields.Title: Jump to: [Cuno: ""How are you gonna *get* to the isl..."]
You: ""Time to go to the fucking island.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Time to go to the fucking island."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Oh, oh!" The kid gets excited. "Cu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, oh!" The kid gets excited. "Cuno knows this shit -- ballistics shit, Science Radio shit. Shows where the shot came from."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is ballistics. She's left a t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is ballistics. She's left a trajectory for us..." The lieutenant tests the thread with his finger. Drawn taut, it rebounds instantly.

fields.Title: You: ""This is also a location we have ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also a location we have yet to rule out." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The golden light melts away into th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The golden light melts away into the blue, glassy darkness of your mind. In it are two neon lit shapes: a man and a woman on the single bed.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Again with this. You're not some ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Again with this. You're not some kind of super-detective. Question people, bust a lip open. Leave this glass cathedral of ballistics to the smart boys.

fields.Title: You: ""How did she know how to do this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How did she know how to do this?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Of course." He nods. "Of course I'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course." He nods. "Of course I'm in." He takes a second to gather himself, then says...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We could ask around in the fishing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We could ask around in the fishing village. They had boats."
fields.Alternate1: "We should ask around the fishing village down the coast. There was a fisherwoman who was tarring a boat."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Does Cuno look like a fucking bino..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Does Cuno look like a fucking bino to you? Cuno doesn't know this shit. Fucking book-shit." He seems unpleased with his lack of knowledge.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Won't work? Sounds like you're avo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Won't work? Sounds like you're avoidin' the truth, pig..." He looks out across the water.
fields.Alternate1: "Sounds like you're avoidin' the truth, pig." The wind blows in from the open window.

fields.Title: Logic: "This is amateur ballistics. She lef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is amateur ballistics. She left a trajectory for you...

fields.Title: Endurance: "He will. He has it in him."
fields.Dialogue Text: He will. He has it in him.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "Why not? Military fortifications ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why not? Military fortifications are made for that kind of thing.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Yes, that one. Cold wind is seeping..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, that one. Cold wind is seeping in right now -- just one floor below you, messing up your concentration here.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Ending him."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ending him.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You would need a map for that -- a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You would need a map for that -- a map of Martinaise.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "One-point-two kilometres away. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: One-point-two kilometres away. The least likely of these positions, let's say 3%. A truly skilled sniper could have done it, possibly from a tent? No... too far fetched.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The island in the bay."
fields.Dialogue Text: The island in the bay.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Unless she thinks the perpetrator..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Unless she thinks the perpetrator was standing *on* the ring antenna, that is where the thread seems to point." He nods.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm going to the island  -- are yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm going to the island  -- are you in?" (Go.)

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind, I don't know what I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind, I don't know what I'm thinking here."

fields.Title: Half Light: "He senses danger. Possibly a trap?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He senses danger. Possibly a trap? You shouldn't ignore this -- the kid's got serious street smarts.

fields.Title: You: "This is also the only point of orig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is also the only point of origin I haven't ruled out yet... (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: You: ""Wait -- I think the shot came from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait -- I think the shot came from the *island*?"

fields.Title: You: ""This window was recently replaced.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "This window was recently replaced."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "I think it was established that *yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I think it was established that *you* did it. Anyway.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "A two-hearted spider."
fields.Dialogue Text: A two-hearted spider.

fields.Title: You: "Have a look at point B' -- the boar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have a look at point B' -- the boardwalk.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "One kilometre away. An unlikely poi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: One kilometre away. An unlikely point of origin, beyond the docks somewhere -- on an islet in the Bay of Martinaise perhaps? There *are* islets there, badly charted as they may be.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay. Well, we should see if there..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. Well, we should see if there is gunshot residue or sniper nests if we go down the coast. Rule these spots out -- one by one."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""From where, precisely?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "From where, precisely?"

fields.Title: You: "Where does the thread lead?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Where does the thread lead?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Maybe if you extrapolate all possib..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe if you extrapolate all possible points of origin first, the thread will make sense?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I just haven't gotten a lot of sle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I just haven't gotten a lot of sleep these past few days."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""How do we get there? Joyce Messier..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do we get there? Joyce Messier had her sloop, but she's gone."

fields.Title: You: ""There are ruins on that islet. A s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There are ruins on that islet. A sunken seafort. I saw it in the coin operated viewer."

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe someone in the fishing villa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe someone in the fishing village can help?"

fields.Title: You: ""It won't work. There must be somet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It won't work. There must be something else I missed."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There, across the grey water -- ami..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There, across the grey water -- amidst crumbling concrete, a birch tree... the ruins of a flak tower, remember?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Obviously."
fields.Dialogue Text: Obviously.

fields.Title: You: ""There are ruins on that islet. A s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There are ruins on that islet. A sunken seafort. I saw it through the coin operated viewer."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Of course. It's where the threads a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course. It's where the threads all meet...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You don't know when to quit, do you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't know when to quit, do you?

fields.Title: You: ""There was a map on sale in the boo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There was a map on sale in the bookstore, wasn't there? A map of Martinaise? We need one."

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind, I don't know what I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind, I don't know what I'm thinking here."

fields.Title: You: ""Is she trying to tell us the shot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is she trying to tell us the shot came from the islet?"

fields.Title: You: ""There are *ruins* on that islet. A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There are *ruins* on that islet. A sunken seafort. I saw it through the coin operated viewer."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I remember." He looks out the wind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I remember." He looks out the window and onto the bay.

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe someone in the fishing villa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe someone in the fishing village can help? The clump of houses on the coast?"

fields.Title: You: ""Lilienne, the Net Picker. She's ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lilienne, the Net Picker. She's tarring her boat..."

fields.Title: You: ""I remember an anti-aircraft gun. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I remember an anti-aircraft gun. The ruins of one... on the island."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""There's this lady in the village....."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's this lady in the village... she..." He pauses, then mumbles: "Uh, yeah, there are boats there... You go. Do shit there, you'll get one. On the coast."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Islet? Like a gimp-island?" He thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Islet? Like a gimp-island?" He thinks. "I think you're on to something. The shot could've come from there..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like it, yes." He adjusts hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like it, yes." He adjusts his glasses.

fields.Title: You: "Have a look at point A' -- the roof..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have a look at point A' -- the roof.

fields.Title: You: "Could there have been another point..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could there have been another point of origin -- further away? (Conclude.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No-no. We're onto something... The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no. We're onto something... There was a map in the bookstore. We should come back with it, compare the landscape to the radius of the shot."

fields.Title: You: ""Let's say: B prime (the boardwalk)..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's say: B prime (the boardwalk); B double prime (Land's End); B triple prime (the islet)."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. You're right. We have to go to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. You're right. We have to go to the island. Pardon me, the concussion..." He takes a second to gather himself, then says...

fields.Title: You: ""Of course we don't *trust* her.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course we don't *trust* her."

fields.Title: You: ""This is also the only point of ori..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also the only point of origin I haven't ruled out yet." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == true

fields.Title: You: ""This is also one of the few places..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also one of the few places in Martinaise I haven't been to." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"]  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There were skiffs in the fishing vi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There were skiffs in the fishing village. You should ask around.

fields.Title: Cuno: "The boy breathes on the glass and w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The boy breathes on the glass and writes something on the fogged up surface, then wipes it all away with his sleeve.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The bookstore. They have maps." Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The bookstore. They have maps." The lieutenant leans closer. "You're thinking what if the shot didn't come from the roof, right?"

fields.Title: You: "Shouldn't there be gun residue outs..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shouldn't there be gun residue outside?

fields.Title: Logic: "This would explain why no one heard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This would explain why no one heard the gunshot -- the bullet came from far away.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, do you think the shot could h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, do you think the shot could have come from further than the roof? In Martinaise?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Oh, oh!" The kid gets excited. "Cu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, oh!" The kid gets excited. "Cuno knows this shit -- ballistics shit, Science Radio shit. Shows where the shot came from."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "No. We're not failing this. You did..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. We're not failing this. You didn't get shot for nothing. Close your eyes and open them -- you can do this. You've done it before.

fields.Title: You: ""This is also a location I have yet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is also a location I have yet to rule out." (Proceed.)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["whirling.replaced_open_two_other_opts"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_boardwalk_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.check_lands_end_done"] == false

fields.Title: You: ""Looks like we need to go to the is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like we need to go to the island."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There were boats there. You should..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There were boats there. You should ask around.
